Simon made a sound that, for a rat, sounded a lot like a snort. Jace didn't seem to hear it.

They were stumbling up the steps as rapidly as they dared. The flight rose in a high spiral, up through the building. They passed landing after landing, but no doors. They had reached the fourth

featureless turn when a muffled explosion rocked the stairwell, and a cloud of dust billowed upward.

